description.p:
Embodiments will now be described, by way of example, with reference to the accompanying figures in which:
Figure 1 is a sectional view of a marine azimuth thruster;
Figure 2 shows a wireless communication system installed in the thruster of Figure 1;
Figure 3 shows a re-radiating element of the wireless communication system;
Figures 4a and 4b show possible configurations of transmitters and receivers of the wireless communication system;
Figure 5 shows a wireless communication system installed in a gas turbine engine; and
Figure 6 shows a thermoelectric element of the wireless communication system.

claim.claim-text:
A wireless communication system (401) for a marine propulsor (101), comprising:
a transmitter (401 b);
a receiver (401 c); and
a waveguide (401 a), arranged to convey an electromagnetic data signal between the transmitter and the receiver;
wherein the waveguide comprises an electrically non-conductive solid or liquid medium for propagating the electromagnetic data signal.
